Squiz/CommentedOutCode: prevent parsing out valid code.

The regex used to parse out comment fencing was a little too overactive and would change the below commented out code:
```php
//eval('$var = 4;');
```
to
```php
//eval('$var - ;');
```

Now only real comment fencing for which this regex was intended will be replaced.

Added T_CLOSE_PARENTHESIS to function name tokens

It is possible only on PHP7+

(function($a, $b) {
  echo $a, $b;
})('a', 'b');

Update File.php

# Removed unused statement : $sniff     = $code;
# Removed unused variable $isWin and logic to set that value

Fix Bug #20381

code was treating this all as one comment
/*
block
*/
// inline

short ternary operator doesn't need spaces

The short ternary operator '?:' is an inline if followed by an inline
else and does not have a whitespace:

    $foo = $bar ?: false;
